studyProtocolVersions.officialTitle:
A Phase 3 Study of Nasal Glucagon (LY900018) Compared to Intramuscular Glucagon for Treatment of
Insulin-induced Hypoglycemia in Japanese Patients with Diabetes Mellitus

studyDesigns.name: Study Design 1
studyDesigns.description: The main design for the study

studyObjectives.objectiveDescription:
To demonstrate that 3 mg LY900018 is non-inferior to 1 mg IMG for the proportion of patients achieving
treatment success from insulin-induced hypoglycemia using a non-inferiority margin of 10%

objectiveEndpoints.endpointDescription:
The proportion of patients achieving treatment success defined as either an increase in PG to >70 mg/dL or an increase of >20 mg/dL from nadir within 30 minutes after administration of glucagon. The nadir is defined
as the minimum PG value at the time of or within 10 minutes following glucagon administration.

studyObjectives.objectiveDescription: To compare the safety and tolerability of 3 mg LY900018 with 1 mg IMG

objectiveEndpoints.endpointDescription:
SAE, TEAEs (including gastrointestinal, nasal,
and non-nasal AEs), vital signs

studyObjectives.objectiveDescription:
To characterize the PK profile of 3 mg LY900018
compared to 1 mg IMG

objectiveEndpoints.endpointDescription: PK parameters include AUC, Cmax, Tmax

studyObjectives.objectiveDescription:
To characterize the PD profile of 3 mg LY900018
compared to 1 mg IMG

objectiveEndpoints.endpointDescription: PD parameters include BGmax and Tmax
